{{Infobox person | name = Mike Boich | image = MikeBoich.jpeg | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | education = | occupation = | spouse = | parents = | children = }}
'''Mike Boich''' was a major figure at [[Apple Computer]] who was in charge of demonstrating the first Macintosh to software developers and potential customers.<ref>{{cite web|last=Boich|first=Mike|title=Interview with Mike Boich as Apple turns 30|url=http://blog.sfgate.com/chroncast/2006/03/25/interview-with-mike-boich-as-apple-turns-30/|publisher=sfgate.com|accessdate=4 May 2014}}</ref><ref>Andy Hertzfeld, December 2005, O'Reilly Publishing, [https://books.google.com/books?id=Q5m19ocQlGsC&pg=PT335 Revolution in the Valley], (book) accessed June 9, 2014</ref> He is notable as a [[technology evangelist]] who persuaded developers to write computer software.<ref>{{cite web|last=Boich|first=Mike|title=Macintosh Insiders Ten Years Later|url=http://www-sul.stanford.edu/mac/primary/docs/pr5.html|publisher=stanford.edu|accessdate=4 May 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130622235428/http://www-sul.stanford.edu/mac/primary/docs/pr5.html|archivedate=22 June 2013|df=}}</ref><ref>InfoWorld, April 11, 1988, [https://books.google.com/books?id=5z4EAAAAMBAJ&pg=RA1-PA34 InfoWorld Interviews: Mike Boich], Accessed June 9, 2014</ref><ref>Jay Elliott, Dec 7, 2012, Entrepreneur magazine, [http://www.entrepreneurmag.co.za/advice/staff/hiring-employees/steve-jobss-tips-for-hiring-your-a-team/ Steve Jobs’s Tips for Hiring Your A-Team], Accessed June 9, 2014, "...Someone at Stanford gave Steve the name of Mike Boich, a former Stanford undergraduate who had gone on to earn an MBA at Harvard. Mike Boich ... tackled one of the toughest challenges facing the Macintosh when it was launched, coining the word “evangelists” for people on the team..."</ref> He was instrumental in hiring Apple entrepreneur [[Guy Kawasaki#Career|Guy Kawasaki]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kawasaki|first1=Guy|title=Macintosh 25th Anniversary Reunion: Where Did Time Go?|url=http://blog.guykawasaki.com/2009/01/twenty-five-yea.html|website=http://blog.guykawasaki.com/|publisher=Guy Kawasaki|accessdate=2 June 2014|ref=http://blog.guykawasaki.com/2009/01/twenty-five-yea.html|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/68eyVtkeI?url=http://blog.guykawasaki.com/2009/01/twenty-five-yea.html|archivedate=24 June 2012|df=}}</ref><ref>The Nashville Post, [https://nashvillepost.com/news/2011/11/13/the_go_to_guy The go-to Guy: Guy Kawasaki — the ‘father of evangelism marketing’ — will speak at Belmont in a presentation sure to intrigue entrepreneurs], Accessed June 9, 2014, "...''the father of evangelism marketing''. ... I wasn’t the first evangelist at Apple, though. That was Mike Boich..."</ref> His name is listed — as credited — inside the original [[Macintosh 128K#Credits|Macintosh 128k]].
